        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 5:42AM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 541 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking clusters of thunderstorms
with heavy rainfall moving south at 10 mph across far northwest
Alabama.

HAZARD...Heavy downpours and reduced visibility.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Significant ponding of water and minor street flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Red Bay, Cherokee, Vina, Waterloo, Malone, Posey Loop, Atwood,
Allsboro, Riverton, and Wright.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall with this storm may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
